How can I generate all prime numbers between 1 and 10 using C# code, and then select two of them to obtain their sum?
Here is an example of C# code that generates all prime numbers between 1 and 10 and selects two of them:
List<int> primes = new List<int>();
for (int i = 2; i <= 10; i++)
{
    bool isPrime = true;
    for (int j = 2; j < i; j++)
    {
        if (i % j == 0)
        {
            isPrime = false;
            break;
        }
    }
    if (isPrime)
    {
        primes.Add(i);
    }
}
int sum = primes[0] + primes[1];
Can you provide the sum of the two prime numbers selected by the above code?

### Response:
Sure! The sum of the first two prime numbers generated by the code above is 5 + 7 = 12.

