How can I optimize this JavaScript code to make an HTTP GET request using the Fetch API to retrieve data from a REST API and display it on an HTML page? I want to include query parameters and headers in the request. Also, can you suggest a way to handle errors and display them to the user? Additionally, how can I use JavaScript to format the response data into a table on the HTML page?

### Response:
Here's an example of how you can optimize the JavaScript code to make an HTTP GET request using the Fetch API to retrieve data from a REST API and display it on an HTML page:
```javascript
const url = 'https://example.com/api/data';
const params = { 
  param1: 'value1',
  param2: 'value2'
};
const headers = {
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + token
};
fetch(url + '?' + new URLSearchParams(params), {
  method: 'GET',
  headers: headers
})
.then(response => {
  if (!response.ok) {
    throw new Error('Network response was not ok');
  }
  return response.json();
})
.then(data => {
  // process the response data
  const table = document.createElement('table');
  const headers = Object.keys(data[0]);
  const headerRow = document.createElement('tr');
  headers.forEach(headerText => {
    const header = document.createElement('th');
    const textNode = document.createTextNode(headerText);
    header.appendChild(textNode);
    headerRow.appendChild(header);
  });
  table.appendChild(headerRow);
  data.forEach(rowData => {
